HEADWORD: Tinnitus
<hw>Tin*ni"tus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>tinnire</ets> to jingle.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A ringing,
whistling, or other imaginary noise perceived in the ears; -- called
also <altname>tinnitus aurium</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

